@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Terms of Service";
}

<link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/terms.css" />

<div class="terms-container">

    ```
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: @DateTime.Now.ToString("dd MMM yyyy")</p>

    <p>
        These Terms of Service govern the use of the Pharma Pulse pharmacy management software.
        By accessing or using this system, the user agrees to comply with the following terms and conditions.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Software Usage</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>The software is intended solely for pharmacy and medical store operations.</li>
        <li>Users must ensure correct entry of medicines and prescriptions.</li>
        <li>Unauthorized usage or resale of this software is prohibited.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Billing & Medical Responsibility</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>The pharmacy owner is responsible for verifying prescriptions.</li>
        <li>The software only records transactions and does not validate medical accuracy.</li>
        <li>We are not liable for incorrect medicine dispensing.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Data Accuracy</h2>
    <p>
        The user is responsible for maintaining accurate customer and billing records.
        Incorrect entries may affect reports and compliance requirements.
    </p>

    <h2>4. System Availability</h2>
    <p>
        We strive to keep the system operational at all times, however downtime may occur
        due to maintenance, updates, or technical failures.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Account Security</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Users must keep login credentials confidential.</li>
        <li>All activities performed under the account are the responsibility of the user.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Legal Compliance</h2>
    <p>
        The pharmacy must comply with local drug control and taxation laws.
        This software does not replace regulatory obligations.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>
        Pharma Pulse shall not be held responsible for losses due to incorrect data entry,
        misuse of the system, or operational negligence.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Termination</h2>
    <p>
        Access may be restricted if misuse, unauthorized access, or security threats are detected.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Updates</h2>
    <p>
        Terms may be updated periodically. Continued use of the system constitutes acceptance
        of revised terms.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Contact</h2>
    <p>
        For support or clarification, contact the software administrator.
    </p>
    ```

</div>
